<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: PvP KOS list?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:41 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: PvP KOS list?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1547" TARGET=_self>Halflings also take care of their own</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> There was one instance of a Halfling PKing his own and he was

<BR>&gt; driven from the community. We are beginning to form KOS lists,
<BR>&gt; and race traitors certainly make the top of the list.
<P>Where can one find this list? I'm not a Halfling, but I think that for a working PvP community to form we need to be able to weed out the "bad apples" as quickly as possible. A server-wide ooc community will help breed individual in-character communities.
<P>In my opinion, the "Three Commandements" on Rellos Zek are:
<P>I: Thou Shalt Not Kill Thine OWN Race
<P>This is a Role Playing game. If you want to kill, do it "in character". There is a city full of victims only a few zones away. If you want to go on a mindless killing spree, do it there.
<BR>(In time, faction hits will enforce this rule for us.)
<P>II: Thou Shalt Not Kill Newbies of ANY Race
<P>Creating a Monk and going to Erudin where the weakling mages can be pummeled to death by the hordes is not good for anyone. You want to fight, fine. It is a PvP server. We all acknowledge that. But pick a fight that is at least -reasonably- fair. That's why it's called a "PvP server" and not a "PK server". PvP implies that both sides fight; PK does not.
<P>III: Thou Shalt Not CAMP on Corpses
<P>You already killed them once, when they were fully equipped and able to defend themselves. What makes you think that the fight will be any more "fair" when they come crawling back with no armor, no weapon and few (if any) spells readied? Take your one item as loot and move on. (If it helps, imagine that they are coming back with two or three VERY powerful friends that will kick you so hard that you'll wish you never saw them in the first place.)
<P>Additions welcome.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
